 Governor of Rivers State, Nyesom Wike, on Tuesday led some security operatives to the operational base of  Caverton Helicopters in Port Harcourt, the state capital, to effect some arrests over the violation of movement restriction put in place to curb the spread of Coronavirus in the country. Governor Wike demanded for Caverton's pilots to be interrogated on why they flew passengers into the state.  Wike also asked Caverton to produce all passengers they brought into the state.  It was gathered that Caverton flew passengers into the state in spite the border closure order by the Rivers Government.